HTTP Structure:

                   (from playground/maintenance/webroot)
ggz                (redirect to www)
  +-www            (from www)
  |   +-games
  |   +-admin
  |   +-clients
  |   +-docs
  |   |   +-api    (generated)
  |   |   +-guides (generated)
  |   +-dev
  |   |   +-pics   (derived from www/pics)
  |   |   +-site   (derived from www/site)
  |   +-pics
  |   +-screenshots
  |   |   +-<versions>
  |   +-site
  |   +-utils
  +-dev            (content from www/dev)
  +-mail
    +-pipermail    (current archives, generated)
	+-hypermail    (old archives, generated)
  +-cvs
  +-bugs
    +-mantis       (external, only conf)
  +-live
  +-rankings       (from playground/db2web)
  +-pub
    +-ggz
	  +-<versions>

Services (may be on different physical machines):

http: htdig mail search (on mail)
      mailman subscription and archives (on mail)
      webcvs access (on cvs)
mail: address forwards and project mailing lists
      ggz-announce, ggz-dev, ggz-cvs, ggz-bugs, ggz-servers
live: permanent ggz server and database
      ggzd(5688), xinetd/telggz(15688), metaserv(15689), tracker(10000)
bugs: bug database
cvs:  cvs server

Redundancy:

http: provides no redundancy
      goal: trusted (dynamic) or untrusted (static) mirror
      possible for mantis and rankings, not for webcvs and mailman interface
mail: is supported by fail-over mx (mail.hostsharing.net)
      mailing lists are write-only!
live: is supported by alternative server (uk.ggzgamingzone.org)
      uses another database!
bugs: provices no redundancy
      goal: not needed
cvs:  provides no redundancy
      goal: wait for distributed rcs

Backups:

http: none, maintained via cvs
mail: user-defined for address forwards
      mailing lists: tarball (/var/lib/mailman)
live: database: tarball (/var/lib/postgres)
bugs: database: tarball (/var/lib/mysql)
cvs:  repository: tarball (/var/lib/cvs)
      unscheduled rsync backups
system: tarballs (/etc, /home/ggz)

